WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.674 --> 00:00:10.677
[Theme music playing]

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:01:55.449 --> 00:01:58.452
[Birds chirping]

4
00:02:00.537 --> 00:02:02.581
[Wind blowing]

5
00:02:08.545 --> 00:02:10.464
[Somber music playing]

6
00:02:10.547 --> 00:02:12.549
[Fire crackling]

7
00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:18.764
[Door opens]

8
00:02:48.293 --> 00:02:51.505
[Lively chatter]

9
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:04.768
[Whispering]

10
00:03:11.733 --> 00:03:12.984
[Alicent] You're sure?

11
00:03:13.068 --> 00:03:14.361
[Gasping]

12
00:03:17.239 --> 00:03:18.907
[Talya] With his own eyes. your grace.

13
00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:19.991
[Sniffles]

14
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:29.000
[Sniffles]

15
00:03:31.169 --> 00:03:32.754
Stay here. Tell no one.

16
00:03:35.132 --> 00:03:36.174
Help me dress.

17
00:03:51.565 --> 00:03:52.691
Who knows?

18
00:03:56.653 --> 00:03:57.821
My handmaiden. talya.

19
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.282
Some of the servants.

20
00:04:06.163 --> 00:04:10.041
I saw him last night before he...

21
00:04:13.378 --> 00:04:14.588
[Sighs]

22
00:04:15.338 --> 00:04:17.257
He told me
he wished for aegon to be king.

23
00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:27.559
It is the truth.

24
00:04:28.977 --> 00:04:30.270
Uttered with his own lips.

25
00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:34.524
His last words to me
and I was the only one to hear it.

26
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:36.942
And now he's dead.

27
00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:08.517
[Sighs]

28
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.644
What is it that could not
have waited an hour?

29
00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:11.727
Was dorne invaded?

30
00:05:15.816 --> 00:05:16.942
The king is dead.

31
00:05:27.536 --> 00:05:29.621
We grieve for viserys the peaceful.

32
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:32.540
Our sovereign.

33
00:05:35.126 --> 00:05:36.127
Our friend.

34
00:05:40.298 --> 00:05:42.300
But he has left us a gift.

35
00:05:45.679 --> 00:05:49.808
With his last breath. he impressed
upon the queen his final wish

36
00:05:49.891 --> 00:05:51.810
that his son. aegon...

37
00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:57.399
Should succeed him
as lord of the seven kingdoms.

38
00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:08.952
Then we may proceed now
with the full assurance

39
00:06:09.035 --> 00:06:10.829
of his blessing on our long-laid plans.

40
00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:12.622
[Otto] Yes.

41
00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:15.083
There is much to be done.
as we've previously discussed.

42
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.460
Now. there are two among the captains

43
00:06:17.544 --> 00:06:20.171
of the city watch
that remain loyal to daemon.

44
00:06:20.255 --> 00:06:21.506
Let us replace them.

45
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:22.716
Lord Lannister.

46
00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:24.467
[Lord Jason]
The treasury is well in hand.

47
00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:26.386
The gold will be divided
for safekeeping.

48
00:06:26.469 --> 00:06:29.514
Let ravens be sent to our allies.
riverrun and highgarden.

49
00:06:29.598 --> 00:06:31.534
Am I to understand
that members of the small council

50
00:06:31.558 --> 00:06:34.936
have been planning secretly
to install my son without me?

51
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:39.524
My queen. there was no need
to Sully you with darkling schemes.

52
00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:41.568
[Lord beesbury] I will not have this.

53
00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:43.695
To hear that you are plotting

54
00:06:43.778 --> 00:06:47.198
to replace the king's chosen heir
with an imposter!

55
00:06:47.282 --> 00:06:49.492
[Lord Jason]
His firstborn son is hardly an imposter.

56
00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:51.554
[Lord beesbury]
Hundreds of lords and landed knights

57
00:06:51.578 --> 00:06:52.954
swore fealty to the Princess.

58
00:06:53.038 --> 00:06:55.099
[Lord Jason] That was some 20 years ago.
Most of them now dead.

59
00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:56.392
[Lord Jasper] You heard the lord hand.

60
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.668
Plot or no. the king changed his mind.

61
00:06:59.711 --> 00:07:01.796
I am six-and-seventy years old.

62
00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:06.760
I have known viserys longer
than any who sit at this table.

63
00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:11.222
And I will not believe that he said this
on his deathbed. alone.

64
00:07:11.306 --> 00:07:14.517
with only the boy's mother as a witness.

65
00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:17.562
- This is seizure!
- [Sighs]

66
00:07:17.646 --> 00:07:20.148
It is theft! It is treason!

67
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:23.193
- At the least. it is...
- Mind your tongue. lyman.

68
00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:25.904
The king was well last night...

69
00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:27.739
By all accounts.

70
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:34.621
Which of you here can swear
that he died of his own accord?

71
00:07:34.704 --> 00:07:38.458
Which of us are you accusing
of regicide. lord beesbury?

72
00:07:38.541 --> 00:07:42.921
Whether it was one of you.
or all of you. I care not.

73
00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:44.798
- I will have no part...
- Sit down!

74
00:07:44.881 --> 00:07:46.481
- [Groans]
- [Alicent gasps] Ser criston.

75
00:07:46.925 --> 00:07:47.926
[Gasps]

76
00:07:58.812 --> 00:08:01.940
Throw down your sword
and remove your cloak. ser criston.

77
00:08:04.901 --> 00:08:06.903
I am your lord commander. ser criston.

78
00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:09.239
Cast down your sword.

79
00:08:09.322 --> 00:08:11.908
I will not suffer insults
to her grace the queen.

80
00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:15.161
There was no insult to me. ser criston.
Put aside your blade.

81
00:08:18.164 --> 00:08:19.207
[Sighs]

82
00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:26.131
- Has it come to this?
- Lord commander. enough.

83
00:08:29.843 --> 00:08:32.679
- Let us have lord beesbury removed.
- [Otto] No.

84
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:37.642
The door remains shut
until we finish our business.

85
00:08:41.062 --> 00:08:42.856
[Breathing shakily]

86
00:08:54.659 --> 00:08:56.536
Storm's end is of concern.

87
00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:59.789
We may not assume
the loyalty of lord borros.

88
00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:02.500
But he has four daughters.
all of them unmarried.

89
00:09:02.584 --> 00:09:04.753
- The right proposal...
- What of rhaenyra?

90
00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:09.507
The former heir cannot.
of course. be allowed to remain free

91
00:09:09.591 --> 00:09:11.760
and draw support to her claim.

92
00:09:13.636 --> 00:09:14.739
[Alicent] You mean to imprison her.

93
00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:17.307
[Otto] She and her family
will be given the opportunity

94
00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:19.768
to publicly swear obeisance

95
00:09:19.851 --> 00:09:20.931
- to the new king.
- [Sighs]

96
00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:22.937
She will never bend the knee.

97
00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:25.315
Nor will daemon. which you know.

98
00:09:27.442 --> 00:09:28.818
[Sighs]

99
00:09:31.029 --> 00:09:32.072
You plan to kill them.

100
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.412
And all here accede to this.

101
00:09:39.496 --> 00:09:41.706
[Onnyle] Your father is correct.
your grace.

102
00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:45.293
A living challenger
invites battle and bloodshed.

103
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.462
It is unsavory. yes.

104
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:51.883
But a sacrifice we must make
to secure aegon's succession.

105
00:09:51.966 --> 00:09:54.052
And then there is daemon to consider.

106
00:09:54.135 --> 00:09:55.571
The king wouldn't wish
for any unsavory...

107
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:58.098
But the king did not wish
for the murder of his daughter!

108
00:09:59.641 --> 00:10:01.476
He loved her.
I will not have you deny this.

109
00:10:01.559 --> 00:10:02.977
- And yet...
- One more word

110
00:10:03.061 --> 00:10:05.701
and I will have you removed
from this chamber and sent to the wall!

111
00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:18.034
What do you suggest. your grace?

112
00:10:22.413 --> 00:10:23.790
[Otto] Time is of the essence.

113
00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:29.045
[Sighs]

114
00:10:34.342 --> 00:10:35.844
Lord commander westerling.

115
00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:39.639
take your knights to dragonstone.

116
00:10:39.722 --> 00:10:41.057
Be quick and be clean.

117
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:57.866
I am lord commander of the kingsguard.

118
00:11:01.369 --> 00:11:03.621
I recognize no authority but the king's.

119
00:11:05.415 --> 00:11:06.916
And until there is one...

120
00:11:09.627 --> 00:11:10.712
I have no place here.

121
00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:25.351
[Helaena] It is our fate. I think.

122
00:11:25.435 --> 00:11:27.687
to crave always
what is given to another.

123
00:11:28.521 --> 00:11:32.317
If one possesses a thing.
the other will take it away.

124
00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:33.860
Yes. Princess.

125
00:11:34.569 --> 00:11:35.904
[Door opens]

126
00:11:35.987 --> 00:11:37.655
[Panting]

127
00:11:37.739 --> 00:11:38.948
Where is aegon?

128
00:11:41.659 --> 00:11:43.244
Not here.

129
00:11:43.328 --> 00:11:44.829
He's not in his rooms.

130
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:49.250
[Breathing heavily]

131
00:11:52.212 --> 00:11:53.213
[Alicent] Father...

132
00:11:54.130 --> 00:11:55.757
[Breathing heavily]

133
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:57.300
[Children cooing]

134
00:12:02.972 --> 00:12:04.057
What's happened?

135
00:12:19.656 --> 00:12:22.492
- Your father...
- There is a beast beneath the boards.

136
00:12:22.909 --> 00:12:24.619
Tsk. Oh. my dearest love.

137
00:12:30.917 --> 00:12:32.919
[Footsteps approaching]

138
00:12:46.224 --> 00:12:47.350
[Otto] Ser erryk.

139
00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:52.438
Where's the prince?

140
00:12:53.147 --> 00:12:55.942
Forgive me. lord hand. I do not know.

141
00:12:56.025 --> 00:12:57.652
But you're sworn to protect him.

142
00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:00.321
He exploits his authority
to order me away.

143
00:13:00.405 --> 00:13:01.864
and then he evades me. my lord.

144
00:13:06.452 --> 00:13:08.371
I believe he may have
left the keep secretly.

145
00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:10.622
gone into the city.

146
00:13:11.249 --> 00:13:12.250
Find him.

147
00:13:17.797 --> 00:13:19.382
Take no one else but your brother.

148
00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:22.051
And remove your white cloaks.

149
00:13:22.135 --> 00:13:24.345
None can know who you are
or what you seek...

150
00:13:25.054 --> 00:13:26.222
Including the queen.

151
00:13:27.348 --> 00:13:28.348
My lord.

152
00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:32.478
Bring him to me.
and me alone. ser erryk.

153
00:13:39.444 --> 00:13:40.570
[Door closes]

154
00:13:51.456 --> 00:13:53.249
What is the meaning of this?

155
00:13:56.419 --> 00:13:58.755
[Indistinct chatter]

156
00:14:13.978 --> 00:14:15.605
Guard. Guard!

157
00:14:26.199 --> 00:14:27.241
[Door opens]

158
00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:33.039
Prince aegon's not to be found
within the castle walls. your grace.

159
00:14:33.122 --> 00:14:35.362
Your father has sent
ser erryk into the city to find him.

160
00:14:38.086 --> 00:14:40.338
Ser erryk knows aegon.
He has the advantage.

161
00:14:43.299 --> 00:14:44.884
[Alicent inhales deeply]

162
00:14:47.929 --> 00:14:51.682
I trust again to you. ser criston.
and to your loyalty.

163
00:14:52.725 --> 00:14:54.977
Aegon must be found.
and he must be brought to me.

164
00:14:56.229 --> 00:14:58.481
The very fate of the seven kingdoms
depends on it.

165
00:15:00.483 --> 00:15:03.152
[Whispers] Everything you feel for me
as your queen.

166
00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:07.031
I will not fail you.

167
00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:09.367
[Aemond] I'll come with you.

168
00:15:10.243 --> 00:15:12.662
That would not be my desire. aemond.

169
00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:15.248
If anything has happened...

170
00:15:15.331 --> 00:15:17.500
Cole needs me. mother.

171
00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:20.420
Ser erryk isn't the only one
who knows aegon's doings.

172
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:37.812
- [Bell tolling]
- [Seabirds cawing]

173
00:15:37.895 --> 00:15:39.897
[Dog barking]

174
00:15:47.238 --> 00:15:48.966
[Aemond] Aegon brought me
to the street of silk

175
00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:50.450
on my 13th name day.

176
00:15:51.451 --> 00:15:57.081
It was his duty as my brother. he said.
to ensure I was as educated as he was.

177
00:16:01.085 --> 00:16:04.380
At least that's what
I understood him to mean.

178
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:07.841
I don't follow.

179
00:16:08.885 --> 00:16:10.428
He said. "time to get it wet."

180
00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:15.141
Every woman is an image of the mother.
to be spoken of with reverence.

181
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:28.779
[Criston] Sometime last night.
we misplaced our drinking companion.

182
00:16:28.863 --> 00:16:32.241
Knowing that he has been. in the past.
a patron of your fine establishment.

183
00:16:32.325 --> 00:16:34.577
we thought to inquire here
as to his whereabouts.

184
00:16:35.244 --> 00:16:36.244
And describe him.

185
00:16:37.413 --> 00:16:38.956
That is a delicate matter.

186
00:16:40.541 --> 00:16:43.586
You see. the man we seek
is the young prince aegon.

187
00:16:44.545 --> 00:16:46.839
I may trust. I hope.
in the discretion of your trade.

188
00:16:46.923 --> 00:16:48.132
[Chuckles]

189
00:16:48.508 --> 00:16:49.884
The prince is not here.

190
00:16:51.469 --> 00:16:54.597
Has he been here? Earlier. perhaps?

191
00:16:55.515 --> 00:16:58.226
Quite a bit earlier. Years ago. in fact.

192
00:16:58.309 --> 00:16:59.393
But more recently?

193
00:17:01.187 --> 00:17:03.648
[Woman] He does not frequent
the street of silk.

194
00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:06.567
His tastes are known to be...

195
00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:09.529
Less discriminating.

196
00:17:10.738 --> 00:17:11.906
Meaning what?

197
00:17:13.407 --> 00:17:17.995
I wish you luck. good ser.
And my best to your friend.

198
00:17:21.165 --> 00:17:22.792
[Chickens clucking. crowing]

199
00:17:25.127 --> 00:17:26.212
How you've grown.

200
00:17:29.632 --> 00:17:30.632
[Aemond] Hmm.

201
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:35.972
[Otto] Viserys amended his wishes.

202
00:17:36.556 --> 00:17:37.848
It's as simple as that.

203
00:17:40.643 --> 00:17:42.687
You once swore your banners to rhaenyra.

204
00:17:42.770 --> 00:17:47.441
You must now
pledge them to the future king.

205
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:58.077
I must confer first
with my house on this matter.

206
00:17:59.662 --> 00:18:02.915
You'll not leave this room
without declaring your intention.

207
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:08.337
[Breathing heavily]

208
00:18:13.384 --> 00:18:14.927
I am no oath breaker.

209
00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:20.057
I will not bend the knee.

210
00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:29.317
[Otto] Anyone else?

211
00:18:41.746 --> 00:18:46.208
House fell keeps its sworn oath
to the Princess.

212
00:18:49.795 --> 00:18:50.838
Very well.

213
00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:04.852
[Breathing shakily]

214
00:19:11.359 --> 00:19:12.526
Long live the king.

215
00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:14.320
[All] Long live the king.

216
00:19:28.334 --> 00:19:31.337
[Lively chatter]

217
00:19:46.519 --> 00:19:48.800
[Criston] It seems you were mistaken
as to aegon's habits.

218
00:19:49.397 --> 00:19:53.567
[Aemond] He could be in the hands
of mercenaries. on a ship to yi ti.

219
00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:55.610
He could be dead.

220
00:19:56.445 --> 00:19:59.073
Let us hope. for your mother's sake.
that is not the case.

221
00:20:04.745 --> 00:20:08.749
[Crowd cheering]

222
00:20:15.047 --> 00:20:16.400
- [Man] Let's have a look.
- [Groaning]

223
00:20:16.424 --> 00:20:19.135
- Go on.
- [Man 2] Come here. Come here!

224
00:20:19.218 --> 00:20:20.237
Get in there. you little...

225
00:20:20.261 --> 00:20:23.139
[Crowd cheering]

226
00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:29.687
Yeah!

227
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:32.064
Come on!

228
00:20:32.148 --> 00:20:34.275
[Children grunting]

229
00:20:34.358 --> 00:20:35.526
[Children groaning]

230
00:20:39.822 --> 00:20:40.906
[Arryk] How old are they?

231
00:20:42.825 --> 00:20:44.368
[Erryk] About ten years. I should say.

232
00:20:45.494 --> 00:20:47.747
They have them grow their nails
and file the teeth.

233
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:50.124
Makes them more formidable.

234
00:20:51.208 --> 00:20:52.418
Come on!

235
00:20:52.501 --> 00:20:54.587
Prince aegon spends many
a night in this place.

236
00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:57.798
- Do you see now what he is?
- [Boy screaming]

237
00:20:57.882 --> 00:20:59.091
You've not seen everything.

238
00:21:01.844 --> 00:21:03.763
[Crowd cheering]

239
00:21:07.308 --> 00:21:10.060
- Aegon's?
- One of many. I'd wager.

240
00:21:14.064 --> 00:21:17.067
- [Metal clanking]
- [Chickens clucking]

241
00:21:28.078 --> 00:21:31.582
[Aemond] Here I am. trawling the city.
ever the good soldier

242
00:21:31.665 --> 00:21:34.835
in search of a wastrel who's never taken
half an interest in his birthright.

243
00:21:36.754 --> 00:21:39.757
'Tis I the younger brother
who studies history and philosophy.

244
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.300
it is I who trains with the sword.

245
00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:43.302
who rides
the largest dragon in the world.

246
00:21:43.385 --> 00:21:44.637
It is I who should be...

247
00:21:49.183 --> 00:21:52.144
I know what it is to toil
for what others are freely given.

248
00:21:52.228 --> 00:21:53.395
[Aemond] Mmm.

249
00:21:55.731 --> 00:21:57.149
And we can't find him. Cole.

250
00:21:58.359 --> 00:22:00.694
You are a decent man
with no taste for depravity.

251
00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:02.488
His secrets are his own.

252
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:04.615
And he's welcome to them.

253
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:06.367
I'm next in line to the throne.

254
00:22:07.743 --> 00:22:09.245
Should they come looking for me.

255
00:22:10.120 --> 00:22:11.455
I intend to be found.

256
00:22:12.039 --> 00:22:14.834
- [Grunting]
- [Metal clanking]

257
00:22:19.255 --> 00:22:21.340
[Cranking]

258
00:22:21.507 --> 00:22:23.050
[Arryk] Something must be done.

259
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:24.718
Aegon is unfit to rule.

260
00:22:24.802 --> 00:22:26.887
You tolerated
the prince's proclivities for years.

261
00:22:26.971 --> 00:22:28.639
Because it was my sworn duty. arryk.

262
00:22:28.722 --> 00:22:30.099
It's for the hand to find wisdom.

263
00:22:30.724 --> 00:22:32.852
We swore an oath of service until death.

264
00:22:32.935 --> 00:22:34.353
A moment of your time. m'iords.

265
00:22:36.146 --> 00:22:37.982
You'll find no buyers
for your wares here.

266
00:22:42.069 --> 00:22:43.571
I can take you to prince aegon.

267
00:22:45.906 --> 00:22:47.992
Rather. I am sent by one
who knows where he is.

268
00:22:48.951 --> 00:22:50.911
Who'll tell you. for a price.

269
00:22:52.496 --> 00:22:55.541
Deliver him.
and we'll consider your price.

270
00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:58.711
My mistress will not
treat with the servants of the keep.

271
00:23:00.170 --> 00:23:01.547
exalted though they may be.

272
00:23:03.132 --> 00:23:05.426
She'll trust this
to the hand of the king only.

273
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:06.509
Impossible.

274
00:23:08.387 --> 00:23:11.265
I think he will wish to hear
what the white worm can tell him.

275
00:23:20.316 --> 00:23:23.527
- [Bell tolling]
- [Gate creaking]

276
00:23:27.072 --> 00:23:29.575
[Guard] Halt! Hold the gate!

277
00:23:29.658 --> 00:23:31.410
[Horse neighs]

278
00:23:31.493 --> 00:23:32.411
[Grunts]

279
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:33.621
[Lord caswell] Let go of me!

280
00:23:33.704 --> 00:23:35.497
[Larys] He was fleeing from the gate.

281
00:23:35.581 --> 00:23:36.641
[Lord caswell] Do you know who I am?

282
00:23:36.665 --> 00:23:38.751
[Larys] A warning for the Princess.
I 'd wager.

283
00:23:41.170 --> 00:23:42.296
What say you?

284
00:23:43.589 --> 00:23:45.799
The lord confessor presumes.

285
00:23:48.218 --> 00:23:50.304
I have no love for the Princess.

286
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:53.098
[Otto] And where were you going then
with such urgency?

287
00:23:59.813 --> 00:24:01.815
Let the king's justice take him.

288
00:24:02.775 --> 00:24:04.401
[Grunting]

289
00:24:06.445 --> 00:24:07.863
[Lord caswell] Let go of me!

290
00:24:07.947 --> 00:24:10.449
- No! This is not right!
- You did well. lord larys.

291
00:24:11.033 --> 00:24:13.744
- [Lord caswell] I will...
- Only my duty. my lord hand.

292
00:24:13.827 --> 00:24:15.221
[Lord caswell] Who do you think you are?

293
00:24:15.245 --> 00:24:17.365
[Otto] You've spent many hours
with the queen of late.

294
00:24:24.254 --> 00:24:28.717
There's no reason those hours could not.
in the end. benefit you.

295
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:38.143
[Somber music playing]

296
00:25:06.171 --> 00:25:08.173
[Somber music continues]

297
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.693
[Sniffling]

298
00:25:40.039 --> 00:25:41.165
[Sniffles]

299
00:25:42.791 --> 00:25:43.959
[Sighs]

300
00:25:48.172 --> 00:25:49.381
[Door opens]

301
00:25:59.266 --> 00:26:01.518
I will do you the considerable
courtesy of assuming

302
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:05.147
there is a good reason for the outrage
of my treatment here this morning.

303
00:26:07.066 --> 00:26:09.401
My sincerest regrets
for the lack of ceremony.

304
00:26:12.738 --> 00:26:13.822
The king.

305
00:26:15.532 --> 00:26:16.700
[Sighs]

306
00:26:19.912 --> 00:26:21.705
And you are usurping the throne.

307
00:26:21.789 --> 00:26:23.665
It was my husband's dying wish.

308
00:26:23.791 --> 00:26:25.501
- [Scoffs]
- [Alicent] Believe it or no.

309
00:26:25.584 --> 00:26:27.044
it is of no consequence.

310
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:28.879
Aegon will be king.

311
00:26:32.508 --> 00:26:34.218
I came here to ask your support.

312
00:26:35.260 --> 00:26:37.471
Well. I must credit you
for your boldness.

313
00:26:38.764 --> 00:26:42.017
House velaryon has long allied itself
with the Princess rhaenyra

314
00:26:42.101 --> 00:26:43.602
and what has it gained you?

315
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:48.273
Your daughter dead. alone in pentos.

316
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:51.401
Your son cuckolded.

317
00:26:51.485 --> 00:26:53.195
Rhaenyra's heirs are none of yours.

318
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:59.201
It is your husband
who grasps so heedlessly for the throne.

319
00:27:00.160 --> 00:27:01.787
And even he has abandoned you.

320
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:04.581
Gone these six long years
to fight a desperate battle.

321
00:27:04.665 --> 00:27:07.417
returning grievously.
if not mortally. wounded.

322
00:27:07.918 --> 00:27:10.546
leaving the lady of driftmark
to chart her course alone.

323
00:27:13.298 --> 00:27:16.051
The word of my house is not fickle.

324
00:27:19.263 --> 00:27:21.265
But. dear cousin.

325
00:27:23.142 --> 00:27:27.354
you more than any soul alive
understand what I say now.

326
00:27:27.437 --> 00:27:31.316
Princess rhaenys. I loved my husband.
but I will speak the truth we both know.

327
00:27:32.860 --> 00:27:34.069
You should've been queen.

328
00:27:36.947 --> 00:27:39.116
I little thought to hear
those words from you.

329
00:27:39.199 --> 00:27:42.035
The iron throne was yours
by blood and by temperament.

330
00:27:42.119 --> 00:27:44.705
Viserys would've lived
his days a country lord.

331
00:27:44.788 --> 00:27:48.750
content to hunt and study his histories.
but here we are.

332
00:27:51.503 --> 00:27:54.798
We do not rule.
but we may guide the men that do.

333
00:27:55.966 --> 00:27:56.966
Gently.

334
00:27:57.634 --> 00:28:01.263
Away from violence and sure destruction
and instead toward peace.

335
00:28:01.346 --> 00:28:02.931
[Scoffing]

336
00:28:03.015 --> 00:28:05.142
Is it in the name of peace
that you've imprisoned me?

337
00:28:06.059 --> 00:28:07.269
And what of my dragon?

338
00:28:07.352 --> 00:28:08.395
If we are overmatched.

339
00:28:08.478 --> 00:28:10.772
rhaenyra will be tempted to strike us.
and war will ensue.

340
00:28:10.856 --> 00:28:11.856
[Scoffs]

341
00:28:12.649 --> 00:28:15.485
[Alicent] Without your dragon.
she may be persuaded to negotiate.

342
00:28:18.280 --> 00:28:20.490
If it's driftmark you want.
you shall have it

343
00:28:21.325 --> 00:28:24.328
for you and your granddaughters
to pass on as you see fit.

344
00:28:29.625 --> 00:28:31.668
You are wiser than I believed you to be.

345
00:28:35.547 --> 00:28:36.965
alicent hightower.

346
00:28:37.799 --> 00:28:41.053
A true queen counts
the cost to her people.

347
00:28:42.721 --> 00:28:45.974
And yet you toil still
in service to men.

348
00:28:46.058 --> 00:28:49.186
Your father. your husband. your son.

349
00:28:51.271 --> 00:28:52.856
You desire not to be free.

350
00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:55.943
but to make a window
in the wall of your prison.

351
00:28:57.194 --> 00:29:02.324
Have you never imagined yourself
on the iron throne?

352
00:29:14.795 --> 00:29:16.421
I'll leave you with your thoughts.

353
00:29:19.549 --> 00:29:21.218
Ring the bell when you have an answer.

354
00:29:28.517 --> 00:29:30.519
[Lively chatter]

355
00:29:45.993 --> 00:29:46.993
My prince.

356
00:29:57.379 --> 00:30:01.341
You yourself are the mysterious
white worm. I take it.

357
00:30:02.884 --> 00:30:06.054
Or are you simply a further pee!
In this stinking onion?

358
00:30:08.682 --> 00:30:11.685
My condolences
on the passing of your king.

359
00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:21.695
[Coins clinking]

360
00:30:26.658 --> 00:30:28.118
[Otto] Where is prince aegon?

361
00:30:28.702 --> 00:30:34.249
I thought. the prince is in flea bottom
where no one is to be trusted.

362
00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:40.047
I'd best secrete him somewhere safe
in case they come looking for him.

363
00:30:40.130 --> 00:30:41.465
Where's the prince?

364
00:30:42.466 --> 00:30:44.259
[Mysaria] He is safely tucked away.

365
00:30:47.304 --> 00:30:51.350
I want an end to the savage use
of children in flea bottom.

366
00:30:52.517 --> 00:30:54.811
They are forced to fight. and worse.

367
00:30:55.437 --> 00:30:59.358
your gold cloaks take
the bribes given them to look away.

368
00:31:00.192 --> 00:31:06.656
An obscenity either tolerated
or ignored by the crown.

369
00:31:08.450 --> 00:31:09.910
I'll look into it.

370
00:31:10.452 --> 00:31:11.453
You have my word.

371
00:31:17.292 --> 00:31:18.960
When your plots ripen

372
00:31:19.044 --> 00:31:22.214
and you install your grandson
on the throne.

373
00:31:23.298 --> 00:31:26.385
remember it was me who put him there.

374
00:31:26.468 --> 00:31:30.680
I could have killed him
as easily as a wasp on fruit.

375
00:31:31.014 --> 00:31:35.769
There is no power
but what the people allow you to take.

376
00:31:38.397 --> 00:31:39.606
I will remember.

377
00:32:03.380 --> 00:32:04.631
[Man coughing]

378
00:32:04.714 --> 00:32:05.714
Listen.

379
00:32:09.428 --> 00:32:10.929
[Man coughing]

380
00:32:12.639 --> 00:32:13.639
[Man groans]

381
00:32:14.850 --> 00:32:16.650
- [Man] No... no!
- [Erryk and arryk grunting]

382
00:32:21.148 --> 00:32:22.190
[Aegon ii grunting]

383
00:32:22.732 --> 00:32:23.984
[Aegon ii screams]

384
00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:28.238
[Aegon ii] Where is the white worm?

385
00:32:29.072 --> 00:32:30.407
[Erryk] She sold you for a price.

386
00:32:30.490 --> 00:32:31.908
And why have you paid it?

387
00:32:33.910 --> 00:32:35.036
I want my mother.

388
00:32:36.705 --> 00:32:39.374
Your grandfather. the hand.
will meet you outside the city walls.

389
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:40.458
[Grunts]

390
00:32:42.043 --> 00:32:43.336
[Panting]

391
00:32:44.504 --> 00:32:47.507
[Aegon ii grunting]

392
00:32:48.341 --> 00:32:50.719
You flee what other men
die seeking. aegon.

393
00:32:50.802 --> 00:32:51.802
[Aegon ii grunts]

394
00:32:57.851 --> 00:33:01.271
- [Bell tolling]
- [Birds chirping]

395
00:33:07.277 --> 00:33:08.737
I do regret this. friend.

396
00:33:19.664 --> 00:33:22.542
[Both grunting]

397
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:26.276
- [Aemond grunts]
- [Aegon ii groans]

398
00:33:36.556 --> 00:33:37.724
[Both grunting]

399
00:33:39.601 --> 00:33:42.187
[Aegon ii] No! Stop! No.

400
00:33:43.438 --> 00:33:46.233
[Aegon ii laughing maniacally]

401
00:33:46.775 --> 00:33:49.653
- I was hoping you disappeared.
- Is our father truly dead?

402
00:33:49.736 --> 00:33:53.240
- Yes and they're going to make you king.
- [Spits]

403
00:33:53.323 --> 00:33:54.616
[Grunts]

404
00:33:54.699 --> 00:33:57.035
- [Aemond] No!
- [Aegon ii] Are you going to help me?

405
00:33:57.118 --> 00:33:58.119
[Both grunting]

406
00:33:59.788 --> 00:34:02.040
No! Let me go!

407
00:34:02.123 --> 00:34:03.208
Where's your brother. huh?

408
00:34:05.293 --> 00:34:06.461
Let me go!

409
00:34:07.045 --> 00:34:08.088
Brother!

410
00:34:08.171 --> 00:34:10.549
[Aegon ii grunting]

411
00:34:15.387 --> 00:34:16.429
Let me go!

412
00:34:16.513 --> 00:34:18.014
[Aegon ii sobbing]

413
00:34:18.098 --> 00:34:19.641
I have no wish to rule!

414
00:34:19.724 --> 00:34:22.352
No taste for duty! I'm not suited.

415
00:34:22.435 --> 00:34:23.770
You'll get no argument from me.

416
00:34:24.813 --> 00:34:28.650
You let me go. I will find a ship
and sail away. never to be found.

417
00:34:32.821 --> 00:34:33.947
The queen awaits.

418
00:34:57.554 --> 00:34:58.847
[Door opens]

419
00:35:05.228 --> 00:35:06.228
[Otto] Well played.

420
00:35:07.063 --> 00:35:08.249
[Alicent] None of this is a game.

421
00:35:08.273 --> 00:35:10.358
And yet you treat it as one.

422
00:35:11.901 --> 00:35:16.990
A charming contest.
the prize. a pouch of silver.

423
00:35:20.452 --> 00:35:21.745
[Sighs]

424
00:35:22.412 --> 00:35:24.456
We have relied on one another
these many years.

425
00:35:24.539 --> 00:35:28.001
And now it is the good of the family
that we both desire.

426
00:35:29.336 --> 00:35:32.297
Whatever our differences.
our hearts remain as one.

427
00:35:34.633 --> 00:35:36.009
Our hearts were never one.

428
00:35:36.676 --> 00:35:37.676
I see that now.

429
00:35:38.303 --> 00:35:40.972
Rather. I have been a piece
that you moved about the board.

430
00:35:41.056 --> 00:35:44.934
If that is true. then I made you
queen of the seven kingdoms.

431
00:35:46.519 --> 00:35:48.730
[Scoffs] Would you have
desired it othennise?

432
00:35:48.813 --> 00:35:49.853
[Scoffs] How could I know?

433
00:35:50.899 --> 00:35:53.276
I wanted whatever you
impressed upon me to want.

434
00:35:55.236 --> 00:35:56.529
And now the debt comes due.

435
00:35:57.989 --> 00:36:00.575
- A debt you were happy enough to pay.
- A sacrifice.

436
00:36:01.785 --> 00:36:04.746
A sacrifice
made for the stability of the realm.

437
00:36:05.664 --> 00:36:07.874
No king has ever lived
that hasn't had to forfeit

438
00:36:07.957 --> 00:36:10.043
the lives of a few to protect the many.

439
00:36:10.126 --> 00:36:12.295
Though I understand your squeamishness.

440
00:36:12.379 --> 00:36:15.965
Reluctance to murder is not a weakness!

441
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:20.678
I have aegon.

442
00:36:21.429 --> 00:36:23.181
We'll proceed now as I see fit.

443
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:27.143
[Alicent sighs]

444
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:32.190
We will send terms
to rhaenyra on dragonstone.

445
00:36:33.233 --> 00:36:36.444
True terms. such that she
may accept without shame.

446
00:36:36.528 --> 00:36:40.156
If she lives. her allies
will mass behind her banners.

447
00:36:40.240 --> 00:36:41.658
looking for her return.

448
00:36:41.741 --> 00:36:42.867
Then she must not return.

449
00:36:44.077 --> 00:36:46.677
My husband would have desired
this mercy be shown to his daughter.

450
00:36:46.746 --> 00:36:47.746
Your husband?

451
00:36:48.581 --> 00:36:51.376
Or you. his daughter's
childhood companion?

452
00:36:53.461 --> 00:36:54.754
[Sighs]

453
00:36:55.922 --> 00:36:58.842
Criston Cole will be named
lord commander of the kingsguard.

454
00:37:00.510 --> 00:37:02.303
My son will be anointed
tomorrow at dawn.

455
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:05.432
The whole of king's landing
must witness his ascent.

456
00:37:06.766 --> 00:37:09.811
He will assume authority.
There will be no more dithering.

457
00:37:10.478 --> 00:37:12.939
My son will take the crown
of his namesake. the conqueror.

458
00:37:13.022 --> 00:37:15.024
and carry blackfyre. his sword.

459
00:37:15.108 --> 00:37:18.611
Let the people remember
the ancient strength of house Targaryen.

460
00:37:22.699 --> 00:37:25.869
You look so much like your mother
in certain lights.

461
00:37:26.786 --> 00:37:28.079
[Sighs]

462
00:37:28.663 --> 00:37:29.789
[Scoffs]

463
00:37:32.167 --> 00:37:33.209
[Door opens]

464
00:37:35.628 --> 00:37:36.629
[Door closes]

465
00:37:37.172 --> 00:37:38.256
As you wish.

466
00:37:50.143 --> 00:37:51.144
[Larys] Your grace.

467
00:37:51.478 --> 00:37:52.812
[Sighing]

468
00:37:55.523 --> 00:37:57.484
The hour is late. lord larys.

469
00:37:59.152 --> 00:38:02.030
I've found out something
that you should know.

470
00:38:07.368 --> 00:38:08.870
[Sighing]

471
00:38:14.626 --> 00:38:17.128
Have you asked yourself. I wonder.

472
00:38:18.004 --> 00:38:19.005
how it is...

473
00:38:19.088 --> 00:38:20.215
[Groans]

474
00:38:20.298 --> 00:38:22.342
That your father. the hand.

475
00:38:24.385 --> 00:38:26.012
found aegon first? [Laughs]

476
00:38:32.644 --> 00:38:34.187
[Sighs]

477
00:38:59.337 --> 00:39:02.215
There is a web of spies
at work in the red keep.

478
00:39:03.383 --> 00:39:07.428
Along its threads
travels news of all our doings.

479
00:39:08.096 --> 00:39:12.267
Your father knows this.
but has left it in place.

480
00:39:13.643 --> 00:39:17.272
More than once. it has proved
advantageous to those willing to

481
00:39:18.940 --> 00:39:21.067
- feed the Weaver.
- [Alicent sighs]

482
00:39:22.402 --> 00:39:23.778
And this Weaver watches me?

483
00:39:31.411 --> 00:39:32.912
[Sighs]

484
00:39:49.220 --> 00:39:53.683
One of the little spiders
is your lady-in-waiting.

485
00:39:55.685 --> 00:39:56.769
Talya?

486
00:39:56.853 --> 00:39:58.438
There are more like her.

487
00:39:58.521 --> 00:40:00.273
Even I do not know their number.

488
00:40:05.320 --> 00:40:08.364
There is one way
to destroy his advantage.

489
00:40:09.574 --> 00:40:12.285
It must be taken out at the head.

490
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:18.833
When the queen dies.
the bees fly without purpose.

491
00:40:20.960 --> 00:40:23.963
Begging your pardon
for the turn of phrase. your grace.

492
00:40:24.047 --> 00:40:25.214
[Sighs]

493
00:40:25.882 --> 00:40:28.217
I assume this task
falls within your expertise.

494
00:40:29.385 --> 00:40:30.428
If you wish it.

495
00:40:32.805 --> 00:40:33.806
it will be done.

496
00:40:59.082 --> 00:41:04.462
[Alicent breathing heavily]

497
00:41:53.219 --> 00:41:54.387
[Erryk] Out of my way!

498
00:41:54.470 --> 00:41:56.055
[Erryk grunting]

499
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:57.515
[Door opening]

500
00:42:01.269 --> 00:42:03.062
[Panting]

501
00:42:03.146 --> 00:42:04.605
With me. Princess.

502
00:42:04.689 --> 00:42:06.566
I cannot let this treachery stand.

503
00:42:42.894 --> 00:42:46.898
[Seabirds cawing]

504
00:42:46.981 --> 00:42:48.261
[Rhaenys velaryon] Where are we?

505
00:42:48.858 --> 00:42:50.109
Just south of king's way.

506
00:42:51.152 --> 00:42:52.361
The Blackwater's this way.

507
00:42:56.699 --> 00:42:59.869
[Fire blazing]

508
00:43:21.307 --> 00:43:22.907
[Rhaenys velaryon] I won't leave meleys.

509
00:43:23.893 --> 00:43:25.996
- If I could get to the dragonpit. then...
- [Erryk] No.

510
00:43:26.020 --> 00:43:27.730
They'll expect you there. Princess.

511
00:43:27.814 --> 00:43:29.023
You won't get past the gates.

512
00:43:30.608 --> 00:43:31.901
Now come.

513
00:43:31.984 --> 00:43:34.153
You must make for the riverfront
and find a ship.

514
00:43:34.237 --> 00:43:35.863
Before they know you've gone.

515
00:43:35.947 --> 00:43:37.615
[Soldier1 shouting] Move it! Go! Go!

516
00:43:38.699 --> 00:43:39.826
[Soldier 2] This way!

517
00:43:39.909 --> 00:43:41.119
[Soldier 3] Keep moving!

518
00:43:41.702 --> 00:43:43.371
That's right. That's right!

519
00:43:45.832 --> 00:43:47.708
- [Soldier 4] Onward!
- This way.

520
00:43:47.792 --> 00:43:49.335
[Soldier 1] Halt! Halt!

521
00:43:52.338 --> 00:43:53.798
[Soldier 3] Keep moving!

522
00:43:53.881 --> 00:43:57.343
[Frantic chatter]

523
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:01.139
[Soldier 3] All of you. move fonnard!

524
00:44:01.222 --> 00:44:03.307
[Frantic chatter continues]

525
00:44:06.435 --> 00:44:07.562
[Soldier 1] Keep moving!

526
00:44:11.774 --> 00:44:14.235
[Sheep bleating]

527
00:44:18.614 --> 00:44:19.782
[Erryk] Out of the way!

528
00:44:21.450 --> 00:44:22.450
Out of the way!

529
00:44:23.494 --> 00:44:25.955
- [Bell tolling]
- [Lively chatter]

530
00:44:41.012 --> 00:44:42.847
[Clattering]

531
00:44:44.015 --> 00:44:45.735
[Alicent] Have the decency
to look grateful.

532
00:44:47.351 --> 00:44:49.437
Do you know what has been
done to give you this day?

533
00:44:53.274 --> 00:44:55.067
In an hour. you will be king.

534
00:44:55.151 --> 00:44:56.694
And my father never wanted this.

535
00:44:56.777 --> 00:44:57.945
That's not true.

536
00:44:58.029 --> 00:45:00.781
He had 20 years to name me heir
and never did.

537
00:45:00.865 --> 00:45:03.576
Steadfastly. he upheld rhaenyra's claim.

538
00:45:03.659 --> 00:45:05.077
He changed his mind.

539
00:45:05.161 --> 00:45:07.205
Oh. [Laughing]

540
00:45:09.957 --> 00:45:11.542
He could have. but he never did

541
00:45:13.127 --> 00:45:14.503
because he didn't like me.

542
00:45:14.587 --> 00:45:15.755
[Sighs]

543
00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:18.132
And yet. with his final breath.

544
00:45:18.216 --> 00:45:21.302
he whispered to me that you
should take his place on the throne.

545
00:45:22.803 --> 00:45:25.473
[Laughing]

546
00:45:41.739 --> 00:45:43.241
Do not toy with me. mother.

547
00:45:43.324 --> 00:45:44.492
I speak the truth.

548
00:45:56.462 --> 00:45:57.505
[Scoffs]

549
00:45:59.548 --> 00:46:00.758
[Alicent] Listen to me. aegon.

550
00:46:02.009 --> 00:46:04.178
Your grandfather. the hand.
will try to impress on you

551
00:46:04.262 --> 00:46:06.138
that rhaenyra
should be put to the sword.

552
00:46:06.222 --> 00:46:08.432
You must reject this counsel.

553
00:46:09.433 --> 00:46:11.310
We must not rule
with cruelty and callousness.

554
00:46:11.394 --> 00:46:14.313
For all her faults. she is your sister.
your father's daughter...

555
00:46:14.397 --> 00:46:15.397
Do you love me?

556
00:46:19.318 --> 00:46:20.318
You imbecile.

557
00:46:21.070 --> 00:46:23.072
[Soldier] Make way
for the royal wheelhouse!

558
00:46:23.155 --> 00:46:25.283
[Crowd shouting]

559
00:46:31.497 --> 00:46:36.127
[Bell tolling]

560
00:46:39.839 --> 00:46:41.215
[Soldier] Hey. hey. fonivard then.

561
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:43.676
[Grunting]

562
00:46:43.759 --> 00:46:45.886
Go on. move yourself! Come on!

563
00:46:45.970 --> 00:46:49.640
[Shouting continues]

564
00:47:03.571 --> 00:47:08.909
- [Bell tolling]
- [Seabirds cawing]

565
00:47:14.707 --> 00:47:17.710
[Indistinct chatter]

566
00:47:21.172 --> 00:47:24.383
[Soldiers shouting orders]

567
00:47:47.615 --> 00:47:49.158
[Otto] People of king's landing.

568
00:47:50.284 --> 00:47:52.328
today is the saddest of days.

569
00:47:53.996 --> 00:47:55.706
Our beloved king.

570
00:47:56.832 --> 00:47:58.626
viserys the peaceful.

571
00:48:00.753 --> 00:48:01.753
is dead.

572
00:48:02.838 --> 00:48:06.050
[Indistinct chatter]

573
00:48:08.427 --> 00:48:11.347
[Otto] But it is also
the mostjoyous of days.

574
00:48:13.307 --> 00:48:15.476
For as his spirit left us

575
00:48:17.853 --> 00:48:20.106
he whispered his final wish

576
00:48:20.189 --> 00:48:24.193
that his firstborn son. aegon.

577
00:48:25.903 --> 00:48:27.488
should succeed him.

578
00:48:28.280 --> 00:48:31.033
[Indistinct chatter]

579
00:48:34.328 --> 00:48:38.666
[Crowd applauding]

580
00:48:38.749 --> 00:48:39.792
[Man] Guards!

581
00:48:39.875 --> 00:48:41.794
[Heavy marching]

582
00:48:41.877 --> 00:48:44.088
Out of the way! Move!

583
00:48:52.638 --> 00:48:53.764
[Guard] Halt!

584
00:48:53.848 --> 00:48:54.848
Turn!

585
00:48:54.890 --> 00:48:55.933
[Guards stomp]

586
00:48:57.518 --> 00:49:04.358
[Trumpets playing]

587
00:49:04.442 --> 00:49:05.442
[Guard] Present...

588
00:49:06.485 --> 00:49:07.570
Arms!

589
00:49:08.737 --> 00:49:11.615
[Crowd chattering]

590
00:49:41.145 --> 00:49:43.314
[Otto] It is your great good fortune

591
00:49:43.397 --> 00:49:47.109
and privilege to be here
to witness this.

592
00:49:48.694 --> 00:49:51.197
A new day for our city.

593
00:49:52.239 --> 00:49:54.283
A new day for our realm.

594
00:49:54.867 --> 00:49:58.871
A new king to lead us.

595
00:50:22.603 --> 00:50:23.771
[Guard commands]

596
00:50:24.480 --> 00:50:25.856
[Guards marching]

597
00:50:57.805 --> 00:51:00.140
[Priest] May the warrior
give him courage.

598
00:51:03.519 --> 00:51:07.690
May the Smith
lend strength to his sword and shield.

599
00:51:10.276 --> 00:51:13.112
May the father defend him in his need.

600
00:51:16.574 --> 00:51:23.163
May the crone lift her shining lamp
and light his way to wisdom.

601
00:51:48.355 --> 00:51:51.442
[Criston] The crown of the conqueror.
passed down through generations.

602
00:51:52.109 --> 00:51:54.028
[Breathing heavily]

603
00:52:09.877 --> 00:52:11.670
Let the seven bear witness.

604
00:52:12.379 --> 00:52:16.050
aegon Targaryen
is the true heir to the iron throne.

605
00:52:16.133 --> 00:52:19.136
[Crowd murmuring]

606
00:52:51.043 --> 00:52:55.005
All hail his grace. aegon.

607
00:52:56.048 --> 00:52:57.633
second of his name.

608
00:52:57.716 --> 00:53:01.428
king of the andals and the rhoynar
and the first men.

609
00:53:01.512 --> 00:53:03.722
lord of the seven kingdoms

610
00:53:03.806 --> 00:53:06.266
and protector of the realm.

611
00:53:08.602 --> 00:53:09.687
[Bell tolling]

612
00:53:09.770 --> 00:53:11.063
Aegon the king!

613
00:53:11.146 --> 00:53:15.901
[Crowd applauding. cheering]

614
00:54:13.542 --> 00:54:14.877
Aegon the king!

615
00:54:14.960 --> 00:54:16.754
Long live aegon!

616
00:54:16.837 --> 00:54:18.046
[Crashing]

617
00:54:18.130 --> 00:54:21.008
[Crowd screaming]

618
00:54:21.717 --> 00:54:24.261
[Dragon screeching]

619
00:54:27.431 --> 00:54:28.807
- [Man screams]
- [Roaring]

620
00:54:35.063 --> 00:54:36.398
[Screaming]

621
00:54:38.776 --> 00:54:40.360
[Roaring]

622
00:54:40.986 --> 00:54:44.782
- [Crashing]
- [Crowd screaming]

623
00:54:58.879 --> 00:55:00.839
[Roaring]

624
00:55:12.643 --> 00:55:14.478
[Doors cranking]

625
00:55:14.561 --> 00:55:18.941
[Crowd screaming]

626
00:55:19.024 --> 00:55:21.276
Open the doors!

627
00:55:28.575 --> 00:55:29.660
Open the doors!

628
00:55:35.541 --> 00:55:36.708
Get helaena.

629
00:55:37.501 --> 00:55:42.464
[Growling]

630
00:55:49.805 --> 00:55:53.517
[Growling]

631
00:56:01.692 --> 00:56:08.073
[Roaring]

632
00:56:15.372 --> 00:56:17.749
[Growling]

633
00:56:24.631 --> 00:56:25.674
[Crowd screaming]

634
00:56:26.884 --> 00:56:28.218
[Screeches]

635
00:56:34.266 --> 00:56:35.559
[Doors shut]

636
00:56:47.905 --> 00:56:49.907
[Music playing]

636
